
                                            The South African athletics star took to Twitter and Instagram to share the good news.

                                         CAPE TOWN – Wayde van Niekerk and Chesney Campbell have tied the knot during a during a low-key ceremony this weekend. The South African athletics star took to Twitter and Instagram to share the good news on Sunday morning. He said: “Can’t wait to spend the rest of my life with you @Neshney.  So blessed to start this next adventure with the girl of my dreams! I love you!”  The 400m Olympic gold medalist popped the question last year during December and posted a video on Instagram captioning it, "She said yes", showing a ring on Campbell’s finger.  Congratulations have been pouring in for the newlywed couple.         So, congratulations Wayde and Chesney!